---
description: Apply scaffolder action patterns when creating new actions. Use when adding features to the scaffolder.
globs: src/**/actions/**/*.py
alwaysApply: false
---

New Action Checklist:
- Write YAML tests first (TDD)
- Create `src/septeo_scaffolder/actions/<name>/__init__.py`
- Define class inheriting from `Action`
- Declare `depends`, `run_preferably_after`, `cli_options`
- Implement `skeleton()`, `init()`, `install()`, `activate()`
- Add `config.toml` if pyproject.toml settings needed
- Auto-discovered — no registration needed

Action Lifecycle:
- `skeleton(context)` → returns `dict[Path, str | None]` (files/dirs to create)
- `init(context)` → post-skeleton setup (default: merge config.toml)
- `install(context)` → dependency installation
- `activate(context)` → guard condition (return `False` to skip)

CLI Options:
- Use `CLIOption` Pydantic model
- Types: `str`, `bool`, `int`, `choice`
- `ChoiceOption(key, display, value)` for rich choices
- `postfill_hook` for context transformation after user input

Avoid:
- Actions that depend on execution order beyond declared deps
- Direct filesystem operations outside `skeleton()` return
- Hardcoded paths — use `self.project_path / relative`
